Glatius,<br>
<br>
First off, before you even consider attacking me -- obviously without even stopping to THINK about what it is I said here -- I would suggest to you that you get your information straight.<br>
<br>
#1 --  I'm not a &quot;monky boy&quot;...my main is an Enchanter.  I happen to play a post 50 monk also.<br>
<br>
#2 --  If you have been reading Monkly Business for months then you are already aware that I'm not speaking out both sides of my mouth here...I have pretty forcefully said the exact same things to MONKS about not complaining cuz another class can do something better than they can.<br>
<br>
#3 -- At no time have I claimed that the folks over at Monkly Business are &quot;choir boys&quot;.  There are some good folks there and there are some pretty pathetic &quot;it's all about me&quot; kinda folks there.<br>
<br>
So...before YOU start preaching to ME about conduct I'd suggest you take a good hard look at your own.  My message is one of unity.  Instead of each classes clawing at the throats of every OTHER class calling for nerfs or lamenting about the repeal of a nerf, I suggest that each class should be more supportive of one another.  Presenting SoE with the vocalized complaints by the HUNDREDS of thousands instead of just thousands seems like a MUCH better way to get them off their collective butts.<br>
<br>
I got no beef with warriors...I PLAY a warrior.  What drives me up the wall is watching intelligent people say and do stupid things instead of forming a united front to combat the problems.<br>
<br>
You bitching at me doesn't get warriors fixed.  You AND me...and your friends and my friends etc CAN raise enough hell to get the problems addressed.<br>
<br>
Now, if what you think will solve the problems is verbally smacking me around, then by all means feel free...personally I don't normally head shot my allies. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.torileighentertainment.com/Andysig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
